NOTICE

PAK-NZE-Julia is an independent open-source replication of the
GIZ-EPRC Pakistan Integrated Energy Model (PAK-IEM 2.0), originally
developed by the Energy Planning and Resource Centre (EPRC), Government
of Pakistan, with technical support from Deutsche Gesellschaft fur
Internationale Zusammenarbeit (GIZ) GmbH under the German Federal
Ministry for Economic Cooperation and Development (BMZ), published
February 2026.

PAK-NZE-Julia is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by
EPRC, GIZ, or BMZ. The model architecture, scenario design, and
calibration approach follow the public documentation of the official
PAK-IEM 2.0; the implementation is independent and the codebase is
released under the MIT licence below.

